No fewer than five people have been confirmed killed while several houses burnt during an attack by unidentified gun men at Zangan village in Takad (Attakar) Chiefdom of Kaura local government of Kaduna State. Mr Bege Katuka, the Interim Management Committee Chairman of the Council who confirmed this on Friday to the Newsmen said the attackers invaded the community around 4pm on Thursday evening and shot sporadically at the innocent residents. “Five persons were killed while two others are still missing. A number of houses including, the new police outpost were burnt and vandalised respectively.” OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY “We have urged the people to remain calm and have confidence in the security personnel that already have secured the area while investigation is ongoing,” he said. Daily Trust reports that Zangan village where the unfortunate incident occurred, bothers Riyom local government area of Plateau State. Meanwhile, efforts to get further confirmation from the State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), DSP Yakubu Sabo failed as he would not respond to calls and SMS sent to him by this reporter. Unknown gunmen kill 7 in Kaduna village Gunmen kill 10 people in Kaduna village Fresh attacks leave 21 dead in Southern Kaduna Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin